# Supabase storage RLS and regex on object names

When `CREATE POLICY` on `storage.objects` validates `storage.filename(name)` (or similar) against allowed file extensions or patterns:

1. **Do not use** the case-sensitive regex match operator `~` for extension lists unless the product explicitly requires case-sensitive extensions.
2. **Prefer** `~*` (case-insensitive) so clients on mobile/desktop that produce `.JPG`, `.PNG`, etc. are not rejected while `.jpg` works.
3. **Keep** intentional exact matches (e.g. legacy `storage.filename(name) = 'avatar'`) as written; only the regex branch should be case-insensitive unless you normalize with `lower(...) ~ '...'` consistently.

Bad:

```sql
storage.filename(name) ~ '^avatar\.(jpg|jpeg|png)$'
```

Good (same pattern, all policies aligned: INSERT `WITH CHECK`, UPDATE `USING` / `WITH CHECK`, DELETE `USING`):

```sql
storage.filename(name) ~* '^avatar\.(jpg|jpeg|png)$'
```

After changing one policy on the same bucket/path, **update every policy** (insert, update, delete) so behavior stays consistent across operations.
